00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:29.370
selecting items from a big group.

00:00:29.895 --> 00:00:31.575
First up, permutation.

00:00:31.965 --> 00:00:35.445
A permutation is simply an
arrangement of objects where the

00:00:35.445 --> 00:00:37.455
specific order is everything.

00:00:37.845 --> 00:00:40.515
The order of the items
matters a great deal.

00:00:40.905 --> 00:00:46.305
For example, if you have three letters,
A, B, and C, the arrangements A, B, C,

00:00:46.394 --> 00:00:53.355
A, C, B, B, A, C, B, CA, CA, B, and C, BA
are all considered different permutations.

00:00:53.715 --> 00:00:57.435
It answers the question, how many
ways can you arrange a certain

00:00:57.435 --> 00:00:59.055
number of items from a set?

00:00:59.565 --> 00:01:03.254
Then we have its school
relaxed cousin combination.

00:01:03.644 --> 00:01:08.625
A combination is a selection of objects
where the order is completely irrelevant.

00:01:08.865 --> 00:01:10.245
Who cares who came first?

00:01:10.545 --> 00:01:15.735
For example, if you choose two letters
from A, B, and C, selecting AB is

00:01:15.735 --> 00:01:18.045
exactly the same as selecting ba.

00:01:18.285 --> 00:01:19.634
It's all one group.

00:01:20.025 --> 00:01:23.655
It answers the question, how many
ways can you choose a certain

00:01:23.655 --> 00:01:25.275
number of items from a set?

00:01:25.755 --> 00:01:28.545
The key difference to burn
into your brain is this.

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:33.509
Order matters in permutation, but
order does not matter in combination.

00:01:33.690 --> 00:01:36.419
Simple, real world relevance.

00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:39.750
And you might ask, where
on earth do we use this?

00:01:40.050 --> 00:01:43.440
Well, permutation and combination
are your best friends.

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:47.639
When calculating the number of ways
