00:03:07.215 --> 00:03:11.865
The factorial of N or N factorial
is just the product of all positive

00:03:11.865 --> 00:03:16.665
integers, less than or equal to N.
And remember, by convention, zero

00:03:16.665 --> 00:03:19.005
factorial, zero factorial is one.

00:03:19.400 --> 00:03:23.120
The permutation formula, which
calculates the number of permutations

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:29.120
of N distinct items taken R at a
time is P of NR equals N factorial

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.340
divided by N minus R factorial.

00:03:31.790 --> 00:03:37.760
The combination formula for selecting
R items from N is C of NR equals N

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:42.350
factorial, divided by the product of
R factorial and N minus R factorial.

00:03:42.925 --> 00:03:47.515
And if you have repetitions, like in the
word apple, the number of permutations

00:03:47.515 --> 00:03:52.225
is n factorial divided by the factorials
of the counts of each repeated item.

